<TITLE> Delwar taken to BIRDEM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 2 (bdnews24.com)  BNP secretary general Khandaker Delwar Hossain was taken to hospital Wednesday with heart and lung diseases. Delwar was taken to the Intensive Care Unit of the cardiology department at the BIRDEM hospital, BNP joint secretary general Nazrul Islam Khan told bdnews24.com by phone. Delwar is also a diabetic. BNP's acting office secretary Rizvi Ahmed said Delwar was running temperature for days. He asked people to pray for Delwar's early recovery. In October, Delwar was admitted to BIRDEM, where he stayed for a month-long medical treatment. BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia appointed Delwar secretary general of BNP on Sept 3, the day she was arrested. bdnew
